      @contract  stashes wireView w's source-tag offset {x,y} (consumer-relative) via wm; decoration only  @ 199
  @api wv:addWire(spec)  @ 203-212
      @contract  appends wire; midi: ports nil; audio: ports default to 1; fires wiringChanged via wm:mutate  @ 202
  @api wv:removeWireAt(idx)  @ 215-219
      @contract  removes the edge at g.edges[idx]; no-op if idx is out of range; fires wiringChanged via wm:mutate  @ 214
  @api wv:deleteNode(nodeId)  @ 222-231
      @contract  removes node and incident edges atomically; no-op if id absent; fires wiringChanged  @ 221
  @api wv:rewireEdgeEnd(idx, side, target)  @ 234-246
      @contract  rewrites one end of g.edges[idx] in place; side ∈ {'from','to'}; target = { id, port? }; port ignored for midi edges; single wiringChanged  @ 233
  @api wv:edgeGain(idx)  @ 249-251
      @contract  live pass-through to wm:edgeGain; 1.0 when ops.gain unset or edge non-audio/missing.  @ 248
  @api wv:setEdgeGain(idx, gain)  @ 254-262
      @contract  writes ops.gain on audio edges[idx]; fast path when poke hosts, else wm:mutate  @ 253
  @api wv:pokeEdgeGain(idx, gain)  @ 265
      @contract  live pass-through to wm:pokeEdgeGain. Returns true if the CU exists and was poked; false if caller must materialise via setEdgeGain first.  @ 264
  @api wv:setMuted(nodeId, on)  @ 268
      @contract  output-mute / read mute for an fx node — pass-through to wm (rm pin-stash)  @ 267
  @api wv:muted(nodeId)  @ 269
  @api wv:setBypassed(nodeId, on)  @ 272
